# UI & Layout Debugging
TRIGGER: User reports layout issues, alignment bugs, overlapping, or elements not stretching properly.
ACTION: DO NOT guess. DO NOT patch visual symptoms first.
FORBIDDEN ALWAYS FOR UI: `translateX/Y`, magic pixel offsets (`right: -20px`), fake/invisible extension layers, absolute overlay hacks.
1. Read `docs/UI_DEBUG_GUIDE.md`.
2. Read `docs/UI_DEBUG_CONFESSION_AND_SUMMARY.md`.
3. Ask user to apply "The Traffic Light Method" (colored borders).
4. Wait for screenshot before writing CSS fix.
5. Debug top-down (root -> parent -> target -> children), keep native flow, one variable per experiment.